text: Dagmar Sandvig (8 July 1921 – 1 November 1989) was a Norwegian politician for the Conservative Party. She served as a deputy representative to the Parliament of Norway from Møre og Romsdal during the terms 1954-1957 and 1969-1973\. In total she met during 30 days of parliamentary session. ==References== Category:1921 births Category:1989 deaths Category:Deputy members of the Storting Category:Conservative Party (Norway) politicians Category:Møre og Romsdal politicians Category:Women members of the Storting Category:20th-century Norwegian women politicians Category:20th-century Norwegian politicians
